anime: YesMix - v1.6 (original), MeinaPastel - V6 ( Pastel )

For the " Seagull's Soar" prompt:

Fu Hua(Seagull),1girl,swimsuit,sunglasses,ponytail, single glove,

For the "Taixuan Impression" prompt:

Fu Hua(Taixu),1girl,chinese clothes,black gloves,

(Please note that the mention of "black gloves" may slightly increase the chance of irregularities in the appearance of the arms or fingers. If precise details are not of utmost importance, the mention of gloves can be excluded.)

¬†

For the "Shadow Knight" prompt:

Fu Hua(Knight),1girl,bodysuit,pongtail,

By adding the phrase "outfit" to the negative prompt, it is possible to minimize the occurrence of peculiarities in the depiction of her limbs or armor.

¬†Additionally, including "3D rendering" in the negative prompt can help reduce the three-dimensional effect in the generated image.

¬†

Recommended weight:0.7-0.9

(When using the " Shadow Knight " should increase to 0.8-1.0)

¬†

This model is based on the "animefull-final-pruned.ckpt",and the adaptation degree of different models can be seen in Figure 8.

¬†

To address the issue of Fu Hua's face not resembling her character, the training process included numerous close-up shots of her face. You may try including the prompt "face" during the image generation process. However, when generating headshots, there is a possibility of the inclusion of Shadow Knight's headpiece. To avoid this, prompt related to Shadow Knight should be added to the negative prompt.

¬†

It is worth mentioning that this model's versatility is limited. If you are interested in outfit changes, the previously mentioned "Azure Empyrea" model may be more suitable as it offers better versatility.

¬†

On an unrelated note:

Although it has been advised against creating multi-character models with Lora, I couldn't resist giving it a try. In fact, the previous "Cerulean Court" model was initially intended to be a combination of two characters but was eventually split into two due to the similarity of their outfits and concerns regarding versatility.

As for this model, I originally intended to include five variations but ended up with only three due to various reasons. The main reason was the excessively long training time. While previous versions typically took between 30 and 60 minutes, this one took 4 hours. Unfortunately, my computer crashed at the 3.5-hour mark, resulting in much longer processing time. Considering the subsequent organizing and verifying tasks, creating just one version required me to devote an entire day. Consequently, it is unlikely that multi- outfit models will be developed in the future.

Thank you for patiently reading my nagging so far! As a sneak peek, the next model will feature Fu Hua in the " Rustic Noir " outfit.

items.name: SB Realistic
items.description:
What to expect

This model can generate photorealistic images of people with decent anatomy. It can also do good images of cities and buildings. It doesn't need a lot of negative prompt, but those can help guide the generation of the image, specially if you want to avoid nudity or sensuality. It's not aimed at NSFW images but it can generate such results.

It responded well to most Lora models I used in conjunction. If you find any issue with a Lora, please leave a comment.

Why I made this

I have a collection of a dozen favorite photorealistic models and decided to merge my most used models. I hoped to get a model able to satisfy my personal taste and demand for both high quality scenarios and characters for my comics.

I don't think this is good to generate icons or game assets. I suggest you use a specialized Lora for such tasks.

The models I used in the merge are:

  • I Can't Believe It's Not Photography

  • ùï¥ùñëùñëùñöùñòùñôùñóùñî - 2nd Ed

  • Consistent Factor v3 Light

  • CyberRealistic v3.2

items.name: Millie (Helluva Boss) [LoRA]
items.description:
This is my first attempt at making a LoRA

I‚Äôm pretty new to stable diffusion altogether, and coming here, I was disappointed that there was no model for Millie yet, so I sought to try make one myself, and the results were too good to keep to myself. Of course, feedback is appreciated.

This was trained in 13 epochs with about 150 images in its dataset. Its training model is AnythingElse V4 and it is also the model I prefer for generating images. If you find any other good models for the LoRA, feel free to share.

Activation word and other useful terms

millie is the activation word

yellow sclera, slit pupils, sharp teeth, vibrant red skin, black eyes, perfect eyes are all very useful terms for improving the face. I recommend activating ‚Äúrestore faces‚Äù if possible.

Using 1girl is very recommended for improved anatomy.

Good things

I specifically chose images I thought encompassed millie‚Äôs design faithfully, and so the LoRA maintains her physique, proportions, and (a bit less reliably) her actual height/size. Of course, you can change all this by prompting it yourself.

Millie (by pure accident) does not usually appear with her tail unless you prompt it with demon tail. This is a happy accident that lets you hide her tail if you think it‚Äôs getting in the way or messing up when there‚Äôs a lot of props, or if you just don‚Äôt like the tail altogether.

Backgrounds can resemble those seen in Helluva Boss if you want some immersion. (The pink and purple striped wallpaper inside I.M.P hq comes to mind)

Millie seems to be pretty good with LoRA‚Äôs that entail actions, poses etc.

Bad things

Because of the way I chose the dataset‚Äôs images, a lot of generated results appear cartoony akin to the animation style of Helluva Boss. You‚Äôll need to shove the prompt bar with buzzwords like beautiful, masterpiece, extremely detailed etc. if you want something more 3D looking. (Although, millie does seem to be pretty receptive to other LoRAs that change the overall style, so you can use that too if you prefer.)

While the dataset does contain images of Millie‚Äôs alternate outfits such as her cat costume, all my attempts at generating them have been unsuccessful. If you find a way, feel free to share.

Backgrounds will be very simple looking unless you prompt otherwise.

The LoRA has a mostly nsfw dataset, so if you are looking strictly for SFW image generation, keep that in mind and prompt/negative prompt accordingly.

I hope you all have fun with this model. I can‚Äôt say it‚Äôs perfect, but as far as first attempts go, it‚Äôs damn good in my eyes.

items.name: HomoFidelis
items.description:
Fidƒìlis = faithful, loyal, true, trustworthy, dependable

Note: Preview images are generated without the use of LORAs.

About

This model is aimed for photorealism but at the same time versatile and flexible with its generations. When I first made this model, I didn't really have any intention of releasing it but since I got so many request for it, I'm doing it anyway. The original base model I made was alright, it was realistic enough. But I wanted to add more versatility and diversity into it so I merge it with some of my favorite models that I've used before..

v2.0

I think it's pretty okay for now with a few minor kinks that needs to be ironed out. But I'm a bit busy with some personal irl stuff now so it'll take a while for me to get to it. Feel free to leave any comments if you find any issues with it. I'll get back to it whenever I can..

What's new in version 2.0:

  • Slightly more photorealistic without sacrificing too much of its versatility

  • Easier to generate different ethnicity and race

  • More diverse body types (skinny and slender is still a little harder to generate without muscles, but I will work on that in the next update)

  • Penises are a lot better now, but prompting for specific penis types (erect, flaccid, etc) and size is still a little wonky. It works fine if your character is completely nude, but if clothes are involved, its basically random and often times it'll default to flaccid.

  • Slightly improved armpit hair and anus

  • Can generate a few basic faces of mainstream actors and celebrities without the need of LORAs

My Settings

These are just some examples of the settings I usually use and it's not really a hard requirement so you're free to experiment and see which setting works best for you:

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ 2M Karras or DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Sampling Steps: 25 - 50

  • Hires. fix: On

  • Upscaler: ESRGAN 4x+ or 4x_NMKD-Siax_200k or 8x_NMKD-Superscale_150000_G (if you have it)

  • Hires Steps: I usually put it at 0 so it'll be the same as Sampling Steps

  • Denoising Strength: 0.25 - 0.35

  • Upscale: 1.5 - 2

  • CFG Scale: 4.5 - 8

Extra Tips

  1. Try to keep the prompts short and concise. No need to fill up the prompts with unnecessary wording that does the same thing like high detail, ultra detail, absurdres, hires, photorealistic, hyperrealistic, etc. Keep it simple.

  2. ADetailer is key if you want to get good looking faces. If you're generating a close up shot or portrait, most of the time you won't need it. But if its a full body or far shot, ADetailer is absolutely necessary unless you wanna get distorted or blurry looking faces. I also highly suggest using this Penis ADetailer if you're working with penis stuff, but only if it's necessary. Sometimes it did more harm than good so only use it if the penis looks off or blurry.

  3. Hires fix is highly recommended, especially for far and wide shots where a lot of details are getting lost. And if you're using LORAs, it is mandatory to use it because without it, the output might look a little blurry and overcooked.

  4. Use StableSR extension in your webui if you have a low VRAM and can't use Hires Fix without getting errors. It's slower, but it allows you to upscale even higher than x2.

  5. Use negative embeddings instead if writing paragraphs of words into the negative prompts. Here are some examples of the ones I usually use:

    • bad-hands-5

    • ng_deepnegative_v1_75t

    • BadDream

    • UnrealisticDream

items.name: portrait
items.description:
This lora is testing the ability to improve the faces of SDXL without significant financial investment

I had only $0.33 left for the runpod - and this money was only enough for this micro lora (80Mb).

Dataset: 300 quality portraits of men, women and children. 10 epochs, 16 neurons. ~30 minutes on 3090,

Dataset example:

Despite the tiny size, there are visible improvements in the quality of hair, eyes and skin. Close-up noise is gone. The lighting is more natural.

There are also negative consequences. The trend towards anime style photorealism, for example:

Desc: anime trends to realism (its wrong), but it remove noise and "blurry"

Lora's at this resolution is not enough for small details, shots in the distance.

I think the dataset should be more balanced with different types of images. This will require more processing time and more substantial investment (more money). I have invested a lot of time and personal funds into training models with zero return on investment. Colorful and Animatrix models, fixing clip skip in RevAnimated and merging algorithm through the cosine similarity (implemented in SuperMerger) - these are my developments.

RevAnimated version info:

My models are free to use, and algorithms under Mit license

I would welcome offers to help fund training SDXL. I don't need money, but I need runpod loans (resources). I will be happy to mention in the description of the model your name and a short text that you provide (64 characters).

By the way - current trends to train SDXL on 1.5 output is totally wrong (by my opinion).

TLDR: I know how to fix SDXL right, but i'm not sure what i need to do it for my money and time (again)
